- Epidemiological situation report, 4 May 2019, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_4mai19?e=f96cddba3b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 3 May 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 1545, of which 1479 are confirmed and 66 are probable. In total, there were 1019 deaths (953 confirmed and 66 probable) and 434 people healed;
- data not available for suspected cases;
- 16 new confirmed cases, including 6 in Katwa, 3 in Musienene, 2 in Mabalako, 2 in Mandima; 2 in Butembo and 1 in Vuhovi;
- 11 deaths of confirmed cases, including 5 community/hospital deaths -- 3 in Katwa, 1 in Mabalako, and 1 in Mandima; 6 deaths at ETC/CT -- 3 in Butembo, 2 in Mabalako, and 1 in Beni;
-12 new recoveries released from CTEs -- 4 from Katwa, 4 from Butembo, 3 from Beni, and 1 from Mandima.

