[3] Response and preparedness
- Sat 4 May 2019. Beni: 4 militiamen killed in new attack
[Actualite, in French, machine trans., edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/05/04/rdc-4-miliciens-tues-dans-une-nouvelle-attaque-beni
[Byline: Yassin Kombi]

This Sat 4 May 2019, 4 Mai-Mai militiamen were killed in an attack on an army position in the town of Senga, 26 km [16 mi] west of the city of Beni, province of North Kivu.

According to the spokesman of the Operation Sokola 1, Major Mak Hazukay, the attackers belonging to the group Mai-Mami Mandevu were neutralized during the attack [on] the position of the armed forces of the Democratic Republic of Congo (FARDC) in the locality.

They also abandoned 2 weapons, including an AK47 and a light automatic weapon, according to the officer. The local civil society that confirms this news has recognized the attackers killed.

Paluku Kavalami, secretary of the civil society of Mabalako affirms that among the neutralized attackers are 2 bikers of the area, a former machinist and a footballer.

The attack was launched at 3 am and "several residents of Songa town fled overnight to Kantine and Runzayi," the source said.

The Mai-Mai Mazembe dissident, the armed group Mandevu is one of the hundreds of armed groups that have been attacking the eastern provinces of the DRC for many years.

--
